ibos.name: ibos

revisions.description: Added SFP all unit values, SFP part and serial numbers.
Added SFP RX/TX power dBm values.
Company name change: In October 2015 PacketFront Network Products was renamed Waystream. In this update all PacketFront were changed to Waystream and all pf* to ws*.
Added sBasePX (BASE-PX) and sBaseBX10 (BASE-BX10) bits to pfSFPTransceiver (see SFF-8472 standard).

Add 100M and 10G SFP information from SFF-8472 specification. The column pfSFPTransceiver has new bits s100BaseFX and s100BaseLX, a new column pfSFPTransceiverExt which is a combination of the 10G Ethernet Compliance Codes SFP+ Cable Technology information.
Added new table pfXFPTable that mirrors the pfSFPTable but with minor differencies in parameter set and interpretation.
Updated company name
Moved pfCopy to PACKETFRONT-COPY-MIB and added environment notifications to the MIB at pfIbosEnvironmentNotifications.
Updated telephone information in contact-info. Reordered revision information. Fixed enumerated types not starting from zero
Moved pfRpm to PACKETFRONT-RPM-MIB Moved pfIgmp to PACKETFRONT-IGMP-CACHE-MIB Moved pfProduct to PACKETFRONT-PRODUCTS-MIB Moved boilerplate to PACKETFRONT-SMI and PACKETFRONT-TC
Added pfRpm
Added pfIgmp
Corrected pfAccounting member types
Added pfVersionString OID
Changed name of pfNeighbourPlatform to pfNeighbourModel. Added OID for ASR10K.
Added missing connector type SC.
Corrected pfPolicyTable entry types. Added description for pfPolicyUseCnt.
Added pfAccounting extensions to the MIB.
Added the ipdConfig object
Updated to reflect PacketFronts new corporate address

wsWritedummy.name: wsWritedummy
wsWritedummy.description: This object is a read-write object that accept an integer. The value written has no effect on the system, but a successful write indicate that SNMP write operations are possible on the target router. The last written value can be read back

wsReload.name: wsReload
wsReload.description: This object is used to restart the target router by setting the number of seconds until system reload. A value of 0 cancels any pending reload. The value returned when reading the object is the number of seconds remaining until reload

wsVersionString.name: wsVersionString
wsVersionString.description: A textual representation of the iBOS version. For iBOS versions after 3.2, this field should be used to identify the iBOS version instead of the old wsVersion OID

wsTempTable.name: wsTempTable
wsTempTable.description: Table of values from temperature sensors.

wsTempEntry.name: wsTempEntry
wsTempEntry.description: An entry for a temperature sensor.

wsTempMeasured.name: wsTempMeasured
wsTempMeasured.description: Measured temperature in 100ths of degrees centigrade.

wsVoltEntry.name: wsVoltEntry
wsVoltEntry.description: An entry for a board voltage.

wsVoltNominal.name: wsVoltNominal
wsVoltNominal.description: Nominal voltage in mV for channel.

wsVoltMeasured.name: wsVoltMeasured
wsVoltMeasured.description: Measured voltage in mV for channel.

wsVoltThresholdLow.name: wsVoltThresholdLow
wsVoltThresholdLow.description: Threshold (low) voltage in mV for channel.

wsVoltThresholdHigh.name: wsVoltThresholdHigh
wsVoltThresholdHigh.description: Threshold (high) voltage in mV for channel.

wsFanTable.name: wsFanTable
wsFanTable.description: Table of measured rotation speeds for external fans.

wsFanRPM.name: wsFanRPM
wsFanRPM.description: Fan speed in revolutions per minute.

wsIbosEnvironmentTrapEnable.name: wsIbosEnvironmentTrapEnable
wsIbosEnvironmentTrapEnable.description: Provides control over iBOS environment related traps.

wsNeighbourLocalIf.name: wsNeighbourLocalIf
wsNeighbourLocalIf.description: Local interface that neighbour is on.

wsNeighbourLastAct.name: wsNeighbourLastAct
wsNeighbourLastAct.description: Time in seconds since last neighbour advertisment.

wsNeighbourCreated.name: wsNeighbourCreated
wsNeighbourCreated.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the neighbour first appeared on the interface.

wsNeighbourPacketsIn.name: wsNeighbourPacketsIn
wsNeighbourPacketsIn.description: Number of PFDP packets received from neighbour.

wsNeighbourPacketErrorsrIn.name: wsNeighbourPacketErrorsrIn
wsNeighbourPacketErrorsrIn.description: Number of erroneous PFDP packets received from neighbour.

wsNeighbourPortsTable.name: wsNeighbourPortsTable
wsNeighbourPortsTable.description: Table of ports of discovered PFDB Neighbours.

wsNeighbourPortsEntry.name: wsNeighbourPortsEntry
wsNeighbourPortsEntry.description: An entry for a port of a neighbour.

wsNeighbourPortTxOctets.name: wsNeighbourPortTxOctets
wsNeighbourPortTxOctets.description: The total number of good bytes of data transmitted by a port (excluding preamble but including FCS).

wsNeighbourPortTxDropPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortTxDropPkts
wsNeighbourPortTxDropPkts.description: This counter is incremented every time a transmit packet is dropped due to lack of resources (e.g., transmit FIFO underflow), or an internal MAC sublayer transmit error not counted by.in either the TxLateCollision or the TxExcessiveCollision counters.

wsNeighbourPortTxBroadcastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortTxBroadcastPkts
wsNeighbourPortTxBroadcastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are directed to a broadcast address. This counter does not include errored broadcast packets or valid multicast packets.

wsNeighbourPortTxMulticastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortTxMulticastPkts
wsNeighbourPortTxMulticastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are directed to a multicast address. This counter does not include errored multicast packets or valid broadcast packets.

wsNeighbourPortTxUnicastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortTxUnicastPkts
wsNeighbourPortTxUnicastPkts.description: The number of good packets transmitted by a port that are addressed to a unicast address.

wsNeighbourPortTxCollisions.name: wsNeighbourPortTxCollisions
wsNeighbourPortTxCollisions.description: The number of collisions experienced by a port during packet transmissions.

wsNeighbourPortTxDeferredTransmit.name: wsNeighbourPortTxDeferredTransmit
wsNeighbourPortTxDeferredTransmit.description: The number of packets transmitted by a port for which the first transmission attempt is delayed because the medium is busy.

wsNeighbourPortTxFrameInDisc.name: wsNeighbourPortTxFrameInDisc
wsNeighbourPortTxFrameInDisc.description: The number of valid packets received which are discarded by the forwarding process due to lack of space on an output queue.

wsNeighbourPortRxOctets.name: wsNeighbourPortRxOctets
wsNeighbourPortRxOctets.description: The number of bytes of data received by a port (excluding preamble but including FCS), including bad packets.

wsNeighbourPortRxUndersizePkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxUndersizePkts
wsNeighbourPortRxUndersizePkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are less than 64 bytes long (excluding framing bits but including the FCS).

wsNeighbourPortPkts64Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts64Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts64Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are 64 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortPkts65to127Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts65to127Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts65to127Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 65 and 127 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortPkts128to255Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts128to255Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts128to255Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 128 and 255 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortPkts256to511Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts256to511Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts256to511Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 256 and 511 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortPkts512to1023Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts512to1023Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts512to1023Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 512 and 1023 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortPkts1024to1522Octets.name: wsNeighbourPortPkts1024to1522Octets
wsNeighbourPortPkts1024to1522Octets.description: The number of packets (including error packets) that are between 1024 and 1522 bytes long.

wsNeighbourPortRxOversizePkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxOversizePkts
wsNeighbourPortRxOversizePkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are greater than 1522 bytes inclusive (excluding framing bits but including the FCS). Note that this counter alone will be incremented for packets in the range 1523-1536 bytes inclusive, whereas both this counter and the RxExcessSizeDisc counter will be incremented for packets of 1537 bytes and higher.

wsNeighbourPortRxJabbers.name: wsNeighbourPortRxJabbers
wsNeighbourPortRxJabbers.description: The number of packets received by a port that are longer than 1522 bytes and have either an FCS error or an alignment error.

wsNeighbourPortRxAlignmentErrors.name: wsNeighbourPortRxAlignmentErrors
wsNeighbourPortRxAlignmentErrors.description: The number of packets received by a port that have a length (excluding framing bits but including FCS) between 64 and 1522 bytes, inclusive, and have a bad FCS with a nonintegral number of bytes.

wsNeighbourPortRxFCSErrors.name: wsNeighbourPortRxFCSErrors
wsNeighbourPortRxFCSErrors.description: The number of packets received by a port that have a length (excluding framing bits but including FCS) between 64 and 1522 bytes inclusive, and have a bad FCS with an integral number of bytes.

wsNeighbourPortRxGoodOctets.name: wsNeighbourPortRxGoodOctets
wsNeighbourPortRxGoodOctets.description: The total number of bytes in all good packets received by a port (excluding framing bits but including FCS).

wsNeighbourPortRxDropPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxDropPkts
wsNeighbourPortRxDropPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that were dropped due to lack of resources (e.g., lack of input buffers) or were dropped due to lack of resources before a determination of the validity of the packet was able to be made (e.g., receive FIFO overflow). The counter is only incremented if the receive error was not counted by.either the RxExcessSizeDisc, the RxAlignmentErrors or the RxFCSErrors counters.

wsNeighbourPortRxUnicastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxUnicastPkts
wsNeighbourPortRxUnicastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are addressed to a unicast address.

wsNeighbourPortRxMulticastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxMulticastPkts
wsNeighbourPortRxMulticastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are directed to a multicast address. This counter does not include errored multicast packets or valid broadcast packets.

wsNeighbourPortRxBroadcastPkts.name: wsNeighbourPortRxBroadcastPkts
wsNeighbourPortRxBroadcastPkts.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are directed to the broadcast address. This counter does not include errored broadcast packets or valid multicast packets.

wsNeighbourPortRxFragments.name: wsNeighbourPortRxFragments
wsNeighbourPortRxFragments.description: The number of packets received by a port that are less than 64 bytes (excluding framing bits) and have either an FCS error or an alignment error.

wsNeighbourPortRxExcessSizeDisc.name: wsNeighbourPortRxExcessSizeDisc
wsNeighbourPortRxExcessSizeDisc.description: The number of good packets received by a port that are greater than 1536 bytes (excluding framing bits but including the FCS) and were discarded due to excessive length. Note that the RxOversizePkts counter alone is incremented for packets in the range 1523-1536 bytes inclusive, whereas both this counter and the RxOversizePkts counter are incremented for packets of 1537 bytes and higher.

wsNeighbourPortRxSymbolError.name: wsNeighbourPortRxSymbolError
wsNeighbourPortRxSymbolError.description: The total number of times a valid length packet was received at a port and at least one invalid data symbol was detected. Counter only increment once per carrier event and does not increment on detection of collision during the carrier event.

wsNeighbourPortSNPATable.name: wsNeighbourPortSNPATable
wsNeighbourPortSNPATable.description: Table of known SNPA on ports of discovered PFDB Neighbours.

wsNeighbourPortSNPAEntry.name: wsNeighbourPortSNPAEntry
wsNeighbourPortSNPAEntry.description: An entry for a known SNPA on a port of a neighbour.

wsNeighbourPortSNPASMCast.name: wsNeighbourPortSNPASMCast
wsNeighbourPortSNPASMCast.description: Set to 1 if SNPA is a multicast address, 0 otherwise.

wsSFPSingleModeLen.name: wsSFPSingleModeLen
wsSFPSingleModeLen.description: Supported single mode fiber link length (m). A value of 255000 means > 254000 m.

wsSFPMultiMode50Len.name: wsSFPMultiMode50Len
wsSFPMultiMode50Len.description: Supported 50um multi-mode fiber link length (m). A value of 2550 means > 2540 m.

wsSFPMultiMode625Len.name: wsSFPMultiMode625Len
wsSFPMultiMode625Len.description: Supported 62.5um multi-mode fiber link length (m). A value of 2550 means > 2540 m.

wsSFPCopperLen.name: wsSFPCopperLen
wsSFPCopperLen.description: Supported copper link length (m). A value of 255 means > 254 m.

wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalLowuW.description: TX output power normal range low (uW).

wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighuW.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighuW
wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighuW.description: TX output power normal range high (uW).

wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowuW.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowuW
wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowuW.description: TX output power warning range low (uW).

wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighuW.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighuW
wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighuW.description: TX output power warning range high (uW).

wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalLowdBm.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalLowdBm
wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalLowdBm.description: TX output power normal range low (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighdBm.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighdBm
wsSFPTXOutputPowNormalHighdBm.description: TX output power normal range high (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowdBm.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowdBm
wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningLowdBm.description: TX output power warning range low (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighdBm.name: wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighdBm
wsSFPTXOutputPowWarningHighdBm.description: TX output power warning range high (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowuW.name: wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowuW
wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowuW.description: RX input power normal range low (uW).

wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighuW.name: wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighuW
wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighuW.description: RX input power normal range high (uW).

wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowuW.name: wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowuW
wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowuW.description: RX input power warning range low (uW).

wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighuW.name: wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighuW
wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighuW.description: RX input power warning range high (uW).

wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowdBm.name: wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowdBm
wsSFPRXInputPowNormalLowdBm.description: RX input power normal range low (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighdBm.name: wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighdBm
wsSFPRXInputPowNormalHighdBm.description: RX input power normal range high (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowdBm.name: wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowdBm
wsSFPRXInputPowWarningLowdBm.description: RX input power warning range low (dBm x 1000).

wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighdBm.name: wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighdBm
wsSFPRXInputPowWarningHighdBm.description: RX input power warning range high (dBm x 1000).

wsPolicyIfIndex.name: wsPolicyIfIndex
wsPolicyIfIndex.description: Interface index of policy accounting entry.

wsPolicyIfName.name: wsPolicyIfName
wsPolicyIfName.description: Interface name of policy accountin entry

wsPolicyUsedCnt.name: wsPolicyUsedCnt
wsPolicyUsedCnt.description: Number policy maps set to use this policy.

wsXFPSingleModeLen.name: wsXFPSingleModeLen
wsXFPSingleModeLen.description: Supported single mode fiber link length (m). A value of 255000 means > 254000 m.

wsXFPMultiMode50Len.name: wsXFPMultiMode50Len
wsXFPMultiMode50Len.description: Supported 50um multi-mode fiber link length (m). A value of 510 means > 508 m.

wsXFPMultiMode625Len.name: wsXFPMultiMode625Len
wsXFPMultiMode625Len.description: Supported 62.5um multi-mode fiber link length (m). A value of 255 means > 254 m.

wsXFPCopperLen.name: wsXFPCopperLen
wsXFPCopperLen.description: Supported copper link length (m). A value of 255 means > 254 m.

wsIbosTempLow.name: wsIbosTempLow
wsIbosTempLow.description: A wsIbosTempLow trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that one of its temperature sensors is outside of the predefined low threshold.

wsIbosTempHigh.name: wsIbosTempHigh
wsIbosTempHigh.description: A wsIbosTempHigh trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that one of its temperature sensors is outside of the predefined high threshold.

wsIbosVoltLow.name: wsIbosVoltLow
wsIbosVoltLow.description: A wsIbosVoltLow trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that one of its voltage channels is outside of the predefined low threshold.

wsIbosVoltHigh.name: wsIbosVoltHigh
wsIbosVoltHigh.description: A wsIbosVoltHigh trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that one of its voltage channels is outside of the predefined high threshold.

wsIbosFanRPMLow.name: wsIbosFanRPMLow
wsIbosFanRPMLow.description: A wsIbosFanRPMLow trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that one of its fans's RPM is lower than the system defined threshold.

wsIbosFanOutVoltLow.name: wsIbosFanOutVoltLow
wsIbosFanOutVoltLow.description: A wsIbosFanOutVoltLow trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that its fan output voltage is lower than the system defined threshold.
